item.description:
I got bored of &lsquo;waiting&rsquo; for an OpenQA openSUSE job to complete, so I wrote this quick and dirty script&hellip;
For the same purpose there&rsquo;s also the excellent and full-fledged openqa-mon, but I took the chance to learn something by implementing a simpler version myself.
#!/bin/sh JOB=$1 if [ -z &#34;$JOB&#34; ]; then echo &#34;please provide job number as parameter&#34; exit fi MESSAGE=&#39;Your job is ready!&#39; JOBURL=https://openqa.opensuse.org/tests/$JOB while : do STATE=$(openqa-cli api -o3 jobs/$JOB | jq .
